cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.CV

The paper uses machine learning algorithms to analyze publicly available data from Instagram to predict the number of influenza-like illness incidents in Finland. This involves analyzing both text and visual content of the posted images. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) which deals with the analysis of social media data. Other likely sub-categories include cs.CY (Computers and Society) which deals with the impact of technology on society, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) which deals with the retrieval of information from large datasets, cs.MM (Multimedia) which deals with the analysis of multimedia data, and cs.CV (Computer Vision) which deals with the analysis of visual data.
